de.kerner.commons.exec
Class CommandStringBuilder

java.lang.Object
  de.kerner.commons.exec.CommandStringBuilder

public class CommandStringBuilder
extends java.lang.Object

Helper Class to build a Command line argument string, which can easily passed to constructor of ProcessBuilder

This class is also useful in combination of AbstractProcessRunner and AbstractProgrammRunner.

Constructor Detail

CommandStringBuilder

public CommandStringBuilder(java.lang.String executable)

Constructs a new CommandStringBuilder. First argument for the command line string to build is passed as argument for this constructor.

Notice: First argument is usually name of executable. Passed in either as an absolute or relative path string.

Parameters:
executable - absolute or relative path to executable binary.

CommandStringBuilder

public CommandStringBuilder(java.util.List<java.lang.String> template)

Constructs a new CommandStringBuilder from given template.

Parameters:
template - template for this CommandStringBuilder. All elements of this List are initially added to the command line string to build.

CommandStringBuilder

public CommandStringBuilder(CommandStringBuilder template)

Constructs a new CommandStringBuilder from given template.

Parameters:
template - template another CommandStringBuilder from which all command line arguments are taken over to this newly initiated CommandStringBuilder.
